OL,3,CThe backlash and fallout the
OL,4,CBirmingham Pub Bombings had on Irish
OL,5,CBrummies
OL,7,FEven at seven, Maurice knew something
OL,8,Fwas odd when he and other Irish
OL,9,Fchildren were not allowed to play in
OL,10,Fthe playground.
OL,12,FAnd it wasn't until he came home and
OL,13,Fsaw his dad when he was told about the
OL,14,Fbombings. It happened half a century
OL,15,Fago but the impact is still being felt
OL,16,Ftoday.
OL,18,FNot just by the survivors and victims
OL,19,Ffamilies, but by the Irish community
OL,20,Fand the police officers.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/11
