OL,3,CThe backlash and fallout the
OL,4,CBirmingham Pub Bombings had on Irish
OL,5,CBrummies
OL,7,FMaurice explained that he was hardly
OL,8,Fallowed out, other than to school, for
OL,9,Ffear of being approached and attacked.
OL,11,FThis was mirrored among other family
OL,12,Fand friends who were Irish. His mum
OL,13,Fhad a very strong Irish accent and
OL,14,Fwouldn't use the bus any more.
OL,16,FHe said the wider Irish community were
OL,17,F'appalled and sickened' at what
OL,18,Fhappened, but there was still hatred
OL,19,Fin Birmingham against the Irish
OL,20,Fregardless.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G7/11
