OL,3,CThe backlash and fallout the
OL,4,CBirmingham Pub Bombings had on Irish
OL,5,CBrummies
OL,7,F"It felt like the world was against
OL,8,Fus...The animosity and the hatred and
OL,9,Fthe fear amongst the community was
OL,10,Fpalpable. And also a sense of shame...
OL,12,F"It's quite ironic when I look back
OL,13,Fand reflect the same hands that built
OL,14,Fthe city then stood accused of tearing
OL,15,Fthe city apart... we literally became
OL,16,Fprisoners in our own home."
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G8/11
