OL,3,CThe backlash and fallout the
OL,4,CBirmingham Pub Bombings had on Irish
OL,5,CBrummies
OL,7,FMaurice saw a shift in tension away
OL,8,Ffrom the Irish community as he grew
OL,9,Folder, saying it may be because people
OL,10,Fhad a better understanding of the
OL,11,Ftroubles in Ireland, and a level of
OL,12,Funderstanding and acceptance of what
OL,13,Fhappened.
OL,15,F"I would have hoped my father had
OL,16,Fstill been alive and been there for
OL,17,Fme. He was, at that age, my hero, my
OL,18,Frole-model.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G9/11
